# AI Slideshow Generator Walkthrough

## Overview
We have successfully built a premium "AI Slideshow Generator" web application. This tool allows users to generate professional slide decks using Gemini 3 Flash, edit them via a real-time Markdown editor, and export the results to PowerPoint or PDF.

## User Flow
1.  **Chat Interface**: User enters a prompt to generate slides.
2.  **Visual Editor**: 
    -   **Navigation**: Slides appear as thumbnails in the left sidebar. Click to navigate.
    -   **Canvas**: The center pane shows the slide with "Apple Basic" style.
    -   **Editing**: Click directly on the title or body text to edit inline (WYSIWYG).
3.  **View Toggle**: Switch between "Chat Mode" (for AI interaction) and "Edit Mode" (full canvas focus).
4.  **Export**: Export to PPTX or PDF using the top-right controls.

## Technical Implementation
-   **State Management**: `JSON Object Model` (`[{ id, title, content }]`). No markdown parsing.
-   **Visual Editor**: [SlideCanvas](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slides_shows/src/components/SlideCanvas.jsx#4-42) with [ScaledSlide](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/ai_slides_shows/src/components/ScaledSlide.jsx#3-59) (CSS Transforms) for resolution-independent 1920x1080 layout.
-   **Theme**: "Light Mode" (Google Slides Fidelity).
-   **AI**: Gemini 1.5 Flash responding with structured JSON.

## Validation
-   **Build**: Production build passed (`vite build`).
-   **Linting**: Fixed compatibility issues in styling.
-   **Functionality**:
    -   API integration verified with environment variables.
    -   Markdown parsing handles titles and bullets.
    -   Export utilities correctly parse the slide structure.

